TITLE: Shared Worker Message Handling
DESCRIPTION: This code defines the `onconnect` handler for the Shared Worker.  For each connected port, it sets up an `onmessage` handler that processes incoming messages.  It handles "message" and "history" types. A new message triggers adding it to history and then sends the whole history.  Requesting 'history' will just send the history to the requesting port.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/worker/README.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
onconnect = function (e) {
	for (const port of e.ports) {
		port.onmessage = event => {
			const msg = event.data;
			switch (msg.type) {
				case "message":
					add(msg.content, msg.from);
				// fallthrough
