TITLE: Entry Point with Dynamic Imports (example.js)
DESCRIPTION: This is the main entry point of the application. It dynamically imports `pageA` and `pageB` using `require.ensure`. The `require.ensure` function ensures that the required modules are loaded asynchronously, enabling code splitting and on-demand loading of resources. It takes an array of dependencies (empty in this case), and a callback function that executes when the modules are available. The callback requires the desired module and then calls the exported function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/common-chunk-grandchildren/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var main = function() {
	console.log("Main class");
	require.ensure([], () => {
		const page = require("./pageA");
		page();
	});
	require.ensure([], () => {
		const page = require("./pageB");
		page();
	});
};

main();
```

