TITLE: Exporting Functions and Implementing JavaScript Fallbacks
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript module imports WebAssembly functions (`add`, `factorial`, `fibonacci`) from respective .wasm files. It then exports these functions, along with JavaScript implementations of `factorial` and `fibonacci` to provide fallback options or for performance comparisons.  It defines `factorialJavascript` and `fibonacciJavascript` recursively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/wasm-simple/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { add } from "./add.wasm";
import { factorial } from "./factorial.wasm";
import { fibonacci } from "./fibonacci.wasm";

export { add, factorial, fibonacci };

export function factorialJavascript(i) {
	if (i < 1) return 1;
	return i * factorialJavascript(i - 1);
}

export function fibonacciJavascript(i) {
	if (i < 2) return 1;
	return fibonacciJavascript(i - 1) + fibonacciJavascript(i - 2);
}
```

