TITLE: Sending Input to Fibonacci Worker
DESCRIPTION: This code sends the input value to the Fibonacci worker for calculation.  It parses the input value from the `fib2` input field and sends it to the worker using `fibWorker.postMessage`. A try-catch block handles potential parsing errors, displaying the error message in the UI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/worker/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fib2.addEventListener("change", () => {
	try {
		const value = parseInt(fib2.value, 10);
		fibWorker.postMessage(`${value}`);
	} catch (e) {
		output2.innerText = e.message;
	}
});
```

