TITLE: Webpack Require Function
DESCRIPTION: The `__webpack_require__` function is the core module loader in Webpack. It checks the module cache, creates a new module if needed, executes the module function, and returns the module's exports. It utilizes the `__webpack_module_cache__` to store loaded modules and avoid redundant execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/code-splitting-harmony/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function __webpack_require__(moduleId) {
		// Check if module is in cache
		var cachedModule = __webpack_module_cache__[moduleId];
		if (cachedModule !== undefined) {
			return cachedModule.exports;
		}
		// Create a new module (and put it into the cache)
		var module = __webpack_module_cache__[moduleId] = {
			// no module.id needed
			// no module.loaded needed
			exports: {}
		};

		// Execute the module function
		__webpack_modules__[moduleId](module, module.exports, __webpack_require__);

		// Return the exports of the module
		return module.exports;
	}
```

