TITLE: WebAssembly Module Definition
DESCRIPTION: This WebAssembly module `magic.wat` defines functions for accessing and modifying memory, as well as getting a random number. It imports a memory object and a function `getRandomNumber` from JavaScript, exports `get`, `set`, and `getNumber` functions. The `get` and `set` functions load and store 32-bit integers at memory address 0, while `getNumber` calls the imported `getRandomNumber`.
