TITLE: Defining Fibonacci Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code defines a function called `fibonacci` that calculates the nth Fibonacci number using recursion. It takes an integer `n` as input. The function returns 0 if n is less than 1, 1 if n is less than or equal to 2, and otherwise recursively calls itself to calculate fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2). This implementation might be inefficient for large values of n due to repeated calculations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/worker/README.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function fibonacci(n) {
	return n < 1 ? 0 : n <= 2 ? 1 : fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
}
```

