TITLE: Webpack Create Fake Namespace Object
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates a fake namespace object. It defines the `__webpack_require__.t` function which is used to handle different module types and create a namespace object for them, ensuring compatibility with different module formats.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webpack/webpack/blob/main/examples/chunkhash/README.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
/************************************************************************/
/******/ 	/* webpack/runtime/create fake namespace object */
/******/ 	(() => {
/******/ 		var getProto = Object.getPrototypeOf ? (obj) => (Object.getPrototypeOf(obj)) : (obj) => (obj.__proto__);
/******/ 		var leafPrototypes;
